[In my experience, those are some darn lucky gauchos.

The function of rain in the epidemiology of anthrax is to float the spores up to the soil surface. There is some evidence that it might also encourage a limited amount of germination and multiplication, before resporulation occurs. The rain softens the soil, and so cattle consume soil while grazing on the new emerging, tasty forage.

A map of Argentina can be found at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_pol96.jpg
A map of Buenos Aires province can be found at https://maps.google.com/maps?q=map+buenos+aires+province.
A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map is available at http://healthmap.org/r/adC-. - Mod.MHJ]
